sentences: Victoria Ellen Bond (born 6 May 1945) is an American conductor and composer.
Bond became an Exxon/Arts Endowment Conductor with the Pittsburgh Symphony in 1978, and in 1986 was invited to conduct the Houston Symphony for the premiere of her work Ringing.
Bond became an Exxon/Arts Endowment Conductor with the Pittsburgh Symphony in 1978, and in 1986 was invited to conduct the Houston Symphony for the premiere of her work Ringing.
She also composed the opera Mrs. President about Victoria Woodhull, which premiered in 2012 in Anchorage, Alaska.
